      "name": "03-parametrize-header-norm.md",
      "filePath": "docs/learn/exercises/03-parametrize-header-norm.md",
      "summary": "Test-writing exercise that has the reader add a pytest.mark.parametrize case set against header_norm.normalise_header's 5-step spec, predicting each output first to catch misread specs (e.g. the 'apis' singularise-guard trap).",
      "tags": ["documentation", "exercise", "learning", "testing", "header-normalization"],
      "complexity": "moderate"
    },
    {
      "id": "document:docs/learn/exercises/04-add-a-config-field.md",
